      <title>North Korea appears to be developing missile-armed submarines</title>
      <description><![CDATA[North Korea may be developing submarines capable of launching missiles, new satellite images suggest.Satellite images show a submarine docked in North Korea’s east coast port of Sinpo with a large rectangular opening in its conning tower. This could be concealing one or two missile launch tubes, website 38 North reported.Missile-launching submarines would be very difficult to locate and track and could attack targets from multiple directions, the report said.If confirmed, North Korea’s ballistic submarine could pose a threat to South Korea and Japan and U.S. bases in East Asia, the report continued.However, experts believe North Korea does not currently have the ability to launch missiles from submarines.]]></description>
