      <title>China unveils glass-bottomed walkway 340 meters above ground</title>
      <description><![CDATA[China has introduced yet another frightening glass structure. This time, an open-air skywalk outside the country’s third tallest building.The glass platform is located outside the 88th floor of Shanghai’s Jin Mao Tower, which is about 340 meter above the ground.It is 60 meters long and 1.2 meters wide. It also does not have any hand rails. Visitors are required to wear helmets and harness attached to the safety bar on the building. A total of 15 people, including two staff, are allowed on the platform each time.Visitors can enjoy the breathtaking view for half an hour but they cannot take any personal belongings other than the clothes they are wearing, meaning no self-photograph opportunities.China has a lot of glass-bottomed structures built on high levels above ground, including the Yuntai Mountain glass bridge that cracked just two weeks after opening and the glass bridge that suspended across the Zhangjiajie Canyon.]]></description>
