      <description><![CDATA[Ohio-based Battelle has developed a vortex gun that can fire electrically charged doughnut-shaped rings of air that could travel at 60 miles per hour for more than 50 yards. The gun could be used to deliver tear gas or pepper spray more accurately and over longer distances. The gas in the doughnut-shaped rings is ionized, which would help particles inside the ring, such as tear gas or pepper spray, stick to the target.]]></description>
