      <title>Plane catches fire during takeoff at Florida airport</title>
      <description><![CDATA[More than a dozen people were injured after a plane suddenly caught fire while it taxied for departure on Thursday afternoon at Fort Lauderdale-Hollywood International Airport in Florida.The fire occurred on a Venezuela-bound Dynamic International Airways flight carrying 101 people. While the Boeing 767 was taxiing for departure, its left engine began to leak fuel and the engine burst into flames at around 12:30 p.m. Before the fire occurred, the pilot of an aircraft traveling behind the Dynamic flight reported the incident to the pilot of the leaking plane, who then tried to turn back to the airport. Seconds later the air traffic control tower caught one of the pilots on the Dynamic flight saying, “Engine’s on fire. Engine’s on fire.” Three of the four emergency chutes were immediately deployed after the engine caught fire. All of the passengers on the aircraft were safely evacuated within six minutes. Fifteen people sustained minor injuries during the fire although one person did have serious burns, according to CNN. Dynamic International Airways says it is investigating the matter and plans to operate a normal schedule beginning on Friday.]]></description>
