      <title>Orionid meteor shower to peak Sunday</title>
      <description><![CDATA[The Orionid Meteor Shower will light up the early morning sky on October 21. The Orionid Meteor shower gets its name because of its close proximity to Betelgeuse, the second-brightest star in the Orion constellation. During the shower, meteors created by tiny bits of rock and metal can be seen streaking across the sky as the earth passes through the debris left behind by Halley's Comet. According to experts the peak of the meteor shower will bring 20 to 30 meteors an hour.]]></description>
