      <title>Mobile app simplifies finding a parking space</title>
      <description><![CDATA[Technology provider Streetline has developed wireless and mobile services that aim to simplify finding a parking space and reduce traffic congestion. With the Streetline system, sensors are embedded into the pavement. These sensors can detect whether a car is parked in the adjacent space. This information is relayed to a computer network. Users can access maps via a smart-phone to find the nearest available spaces. Streetline is also installing wireless devices inside parking meters. The meters send to a computer network data such as how much time is left on a meter. Users can receive alerts and opt to add additional time to their meters, paying via mobile-phone.]]></description>
