      <description><![CDATA[A British man is attempting to cross the Irish Sea on a human hamster wheel to raise money for charity. Chris Todd, 35, plans to make the 66 mile journey in two days in a metal wheel that he built called the 'Tredalo'. The wheel is made of wire mesh and has two floats on either side for stabilization. Todd spent 11 months building the Tredalo in his garden with help from his wife and friends. Todd will burn an estimated 36,000 calories and require 30 liters of water during the crossing. He hopes to raise £20,000 for charity.]]></description>
