      <title>Thieves hit Santiago metro, causing two explosions</title>
      <description><![CDATA[Explosions shook Santiago’s Los Lenos metro station Wednesday night; the work of suspected thieves attempting to blow open an ATM.The blasts which occurred at 10.44 p.m. shocked commuters as the station had not yet closed for the night, metro operations manager Rodrigo Terrazas told La Tercera.The second explosion some six minutes after the initial blast with most the damage occurring to the ATMs and glass panes at nearby ticket counters.No injuries were sustained but told local media reports three masked men were seen fleeing the station and driving away in a car.]]></description>
