      <description><![CDATA[A man was bitten by a shark at Myrtle Beach in what may have been a case of mistaken identity. Ryan Orellana-Moczynski, 25, from St John, Indiana, was swimming on a boogie board about a block away from the 2nd Avenue Pier around 7:45pm when a shark bit him. Beach Patrol Sergeant Phillip Cain said sharks typically feed around dusk and advised people to not swim at that time. Orellana-Moczynski may have swam into a school of fish that the shark was feeding on. He was sent to Grand Strand Regional Medical Center and had successful surgery Saturday night.]]></description>
