      <title>Glass-bottomed pool suspended 35 m high to bridge luxury London flats</title>
      <description><![CDATA[A group of British architects and property developers have unveiled their plan to build a suspended glass pool, bridging two luxury apartments.Enclosed in glass 20 cm thick, the pool will be 25 metres long and 5 metres wide, with water approximately 1.2 metres deep.The so-called sky pool will be suspended 10 stories high, or 35 metres above ground. In comparison, Big Ben, London’s famous clock tower, stands at 96 metres high.The glass pool will connect two apartments of the Embassy Gardens development in southwest London’s new Nine Elms quarter.‘The experience of the pool will be truly unique, it will feel like floating through the air in central London,’ said Sean Mulryan, CEO of the developer Ballymore Group.]]></description>
