      <title>Pope Francis in the US: Pope opts for a modest Fiat and Jeep Wrangler as his popemobiles</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twPope Francis will be travelling in a newly modified Jeep Wrangler for most of the duration of his trip in the United States. However, the pontiff started his U.S. tour this Tuesday in a black Fiat 500L that was waiting for him on the tarmac at Joint Base Andrews, reported the Telegraph.The modest Fiat tops at 100 miles per hour, about 60 miles per hour less than the Mercedes-Benz Pope Benedict used when he was in the U.S. in 2008.The Pope has opted for the Jeep Wrangler to be an open-sided vehicle so that he can be closer to the people. However, this also puts the pontiff at greater risk. The bottom of the vehicle is reportedly fitted with blast-proof technology to protect him in case there are explosives on the road, according to the International Business Times.Pope Francis had also compared the feeling of being inside a traditional Popemobile with a bullet-proof glass enclosure to being stuck in a ‘sardine can,’ and prefers the open-sided popemobile to get closer to his ministry, reported La Vanguardia, an Italian paper.“It’s true that anything could happen, but let’s face it, at my age I don’t have much to lose,” Pope Francis said to a Barcelona newspaper. “I know that something could happen to me, but it’s in the hands of God.”Over the course of his papacy, Pope Francis has used modified Mercedes, Toyotas, Kias, and Hyundais among others as modes of transportation. The Pope will continue his U.S. tour to the Capitol on Thursday.]]></description>
