      <title>Workers find skeletons, coffins in burial vaults under Washington Square Park</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twDozens of skeletal remains were unearthed in the Big Apple just days after Halloween near an area that used to be a public burial ground.According to Fox 5, contractors for the New York City Department of Design and Construction were digging to replace water mains near Washington Square Park earlier this week when they discovered crypts containing human remains three feet beneath the ground.Two 15-by-20 foot burial vaults were discovered side-by-side, each with a wooden door and about 8 feet deep. One crypt contained the skeletal remains of about 9 to 12 people, while the other had wooden coffins stacked one on top of the other, reports the New York Post.Both are believed to date back to the late 18th or early 19th century, and was likely part of a cemetery that may have belonged to one of two Presbyterian churches that stood in the area.Archaeologists working with the city are investigating the vaults and will be focusing on identifying those buried. Engineers are planning a new route for the water main project in order to avoid disturbing the burial grounds, reports NBC.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Washington square park on map2. Construction ongoing3. 19th century New York4. Burial vaults5. Archaeologists studying skeletonsVOICEOVER (in English): “New York City workers were carrying out construction to replace water mains near Washington Square park earlier this week...”“...when they discovered crypts containing human remains three feet beneath the ground.”“Two 15-by-20-foot burial vaults were discovered side-by-side, each about 8 feet deep, with wooden doors.”“One crypt contained the skeletal remains of about nine to 12 people, while the other had wooden coffins stacked together.”“Both date back to the late 18th or early 19th century, and were possibly part of a Presbyterian church cemetery.”“Archaeologists working with the city are now focusing on identifying each of the skeletons.”SOURCES: New York Post, Pix11 News, CNN, Fox 5, NBC New Yorkhttp://nypost.com/2015/11/05/vault-full-of-skeletons-found-under-washington-square-park/http://pix11.com/2015/11/04/old-burial-vault-human-bones-found-beneath-greenwich-village-park/http://edition.cnn.com/videos/world/2015/10/27/ancient-greek-warrior-tomb-discovered-orig.cnn/video/playlists/ancient-discoveries/http://www.fox5ny.com/news/44849964-storyhttp://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/local/Old-Burial-Vault-Found-Beneath-Greenwich-Village-Park--340589992.html***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
