      <title>London gym plans to convert commuter bus into roving spin class</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twBritish exercise studio 1Rebel hopes to run commuter buses in London that double as mobile spin classes. The idea is to combine morning commutes with exercise, helping gym members to save time.1Rebel has yet to receive regulatory approval for the idea. The company is in talks with several bus companies about converting buses into mobile spin studios.1Rebel envisions as many as four bus routes that terminate at its centrally located studio in London. The buses would pick up gym members along the route. Exercise enthusiasts would spin their way through rush hour traffic and could then shower at the 1Rebel studio before heading to the office.1Rebel says it might price the 45-minute classes between 12 and 15 British pounds.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Schematic of bus converted into spin class bus2.  Bus picks up passenger3. Inside bus, spin class takes place4. Map showing routes5. Passengers disembark 6. Passengers enter 1Rebel studioVOICEOVER (in English): “London-based 1Rebel wants to remodel buses, swapping out the seats for exercise cycles.”“The buses would pick-up club members at stops around the city.”“This allows passengers to combine a busy commute with a rigorous exercise routine, ultimately saving them time.”“1Rebel hopes to run several bus routes that would terminate at its centrally located exercise studio.”“Once the commute / spinning class is over, club members can shower at 1Rebel before heading into work.”SOURCES: Mashablehttp://mashable.com/2016/05/16/spinning-bus-london/#T3KoX02t4OqM***For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
