      <title>Chinese jets intercepts U.S. navy plane over South China Sea</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twTensions continue to escalate in the South China Sea with another encounter this week between the U.S. and China.A U.S. Navy plane was in international airspace north of disputed islands in the South China Sea on Tuesday, the Wall Street Journal reported.The EP-3 Aries signals reconnaissance aircraft was conducting a routine patrol in the area when it was intercepted by a pair of Chinese fighter jets. The two J-11 fighters came within 50 feet of the U.S. plane and flew so close the American pilot was forced to descend about 200 feet to avoid collision.Pentagon officials say the issue is being addressed through diplomatic and military channels, according to Reuters.The incident comes less than two weeks after the Chinese scrambled two fighter jets and three warships when a U.S. Navy destroyer sailed near the China-claimed Fiery Cross Reef.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. U.S. Navy plane on the north end of the South China Sea2. Chinese fighter jets intercept the U.S. plane3. Chinese jets get too close to U.S. plane4. U.S. plane descends to avoid collisionVOICEOVER (in English): “A U.S. Navy reconnaissance plane was in international airspace north of the disputed islands on Tuesday.”“The EP-3 Aries signals reconnaissance aircraft was conducting a routine patrol in the area when it was intercepted by a pair of Chinese fighter jets.”“The two J-11 fighters came within 50 feet of the U.S. plane.”“It flew so close the American pilot was forced to descend about 200 feet to avoid collision.”SOURCES: Wall Street Journal, NBC, Reuters, BBC, The Guardianhttp://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-jets-intercept-u-s-spy-plane-over-south-china-sea-1463618824http://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/chinese-intercept-u-s-military-spy-plane-over-south-china-n576351http://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-china-south-china-sea-idUSKCN0Y92ZAhttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-36328464http://www.theguardian.com