      <title>TSA warns passengers to be at the airport three hours before their flight</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twLengthy waits at airport security checks could reach epidemic levels in the United States this summer, when air travel usually peaks.The Transportation Security Administration (TSA) is advising U.S. travelers to be at the airport three hours early, due to long security lines, ABC News reported. The TSA advisory comes after long waiting times resulted in thousands of missed flights and delays in airports across the country.Passengers who come unprepared, or those who bring more than the allowed number of carry-ons, contribute to the delay, the TSA said in a statement released on May 11.But with almost 3 million travelers passing through screening each day, the 42,350 agents employed by the TSA are simply not enough, according to NBC News.More than 700 new officers are set to be hired by June, but union leaders claim it would take at least 6,000 new staff to alleviate the congestion.Currently, the only other alternative is PreCheck, an expedited entry program which allows previously vetted passengers to bypass the long lines, for a fee of $85 to $100, valid for five years. As of March 1, only 9.3 million travelers were enrolled in PreCheck, a far cry from the TSA’s goal of 25 million fliers.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Long security lines at the airport2. Missed flights and delays across the U.S.3. Unprepared passengers one of the causes of delay4. Insufficient TSA agents manning security checks5. PreCheck as an alternative to long linesVOICEOVER (in English): [TITLE CUT - ALL CAPS, TWO DECKS, NO MORE THAN 33 CHARACTERS PER DECK]WHY YOU NEED TO BE 3 HOURSEARLY FOR TSA SECURITY CHECKread this VO for title cut: Flying has never been so frustrating[PHOTO 2: FLICKR / DANJO PALUSKA]“Wait times at airport security checks could reach epidemic levels this summer, when air travel usually peaks.”[CUT 1]“The Transportation Security Administration is advising U.S. travelers to be at the airport three hours early, due to long security lines.” [CUT 2]“The TSA advisory comes after lengthy waiting times resulted in thousands of missed flights and delays in airports across the country.”[CUT 3]“Passengers who come unprepared, and bring more than the allowed number of carry-ons, are partly to blame.”[CUT 4] “But with almost 3 million travelers passing through screening each day, the 42,350 agents employed by the TSA are simply not enough.”[PHOTO 3: WIKIMEDIA COMMONS / U.S. DEPARTMENT OF HOMELAND SECURITY]“More than 700 new officers are set to be hired by June, but union leaders say it would take at least 6,000 to alleviate the congestion.”[CUT 5]“Currently, the only other alternative is PreCheck, an expedited entry program, which allows previously vetted passengers to bypass the long lines.”[PHOTO 4: FLICKR / DION HINCHCLIFFE]“As of March 1, only 9.3 million travelers were enrolled in PreCheck, a far cry from the TSA’s goal of 25 million fliers.”[PHOTO 5: TWITTER @THEARIELSARA]“In the meantime, the rest of us will just have to give up three hours of our lives for a security check that may or may not be effective … Or take the train.”SOURCES: New York Times, ABC, WCMH-TV, Transportation Security Administration, USA Today, NBChttp://www.nytimes.com/2016/05/03/business/airport-security-lines.html?_r=0http://abc7chicago.com/news/tsa-warns-travelers-to-arrive-3-hours-before-flights/1338519/http://nbc4i.com/2016/05/13/tsa-blames-you-for-longer-lines-at-airport-security-checkpoints/https://www.tsa.gov/news/releases/2016/05/11/tsa-shares-summer-travel-tips-travelers-out-newark-jfk-laguardia-airportshttp://www.usatoday.com/story/travel/flights/todayinthesky/2016/05/16/long-tsa-line-strands-450-fliers-overnight-woes-expand/84444322/http://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/feds-work-long-airport-security-line-waits-n573796***For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93]]></description>
