      <title>Selfie fever sparks huge rise in lip surgery</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twA record number of lip surgeries were carried out in the U.S. last year as we all went selfie crazy.More than 27,000 lip augmentation surgeries were performed in the United States last year  a 48 percent increase since 2000  which the American Society of Plastic Surgeons attributes to the emergence of social media and the rise of the selfie, CNBC reported.Fuller, more youthful, or sensuous lips can be produced with surgical implants or the injection of a filler material, according to medical website WebMD.Using an injectable dermal filler is the most common method of lip augmentation these days, according to WebMD. One of the most popular fillers is a substance called hyaluronic acid, which occurs naturally in the human body.When our skin ages and loses its youthful moisture, wrinkles begin to form. However, hyaluronic acid retains moisture in the skin and can be used to shape, structure and add volume to lips.But the anti-aging effects of hyaluronic acid are only temporary. So after about six months or so, you’ll need more injections to keep those perfect selfie lips puckered up.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Plastic surgeon consulting with patient2. Surgeon injecting hyaluronic acid into patient’s lip3. Hyaluronic acid molecules4. Cross-section of skin; skin ageing and wrinkles forming as hyaluronic acid depletes5. Surgeon smoothing over patient’s lips to distribute hyaluronic acid evenly6. Cross section of skin; reversal of ageing process after hyaluronic acid is injectedVOICEOVER (in English): “Fuller, more youthful, or sensuous lips can be produced with surgical implants or the injection of a filler material.”“Using an injectable dermal filler is the most common method of lip augmentation these days.” “One of the most popular fillers is a substance called hyaluronic acid, which occurs naturally in the human body.“When our skin ages and loses its youthful moisture, wrinkles begin to form.”“However, hyaluronic acid retains moisture in the skin and can be used to shape, structure and add volume to lips.”“But the anti-aging effects of hyaluronic acid are only temporary.”SOURCES: CNBC, WebMDhttp://www.cnbc.com/2016/04/19/selfie-craze-causes-surge-in-lip-surgery.htmlhttp://www.webmd.com/beauty/treatments/cosmetic-procedures-lip-augmentationhttp://www.webmd.com/vitamins-supplements/ingredientmono-1062-hyaluronic+acid.aspx?activeingredientid=1062&activeingredientname=hyaluronic+acid***For story suggestions please contact tips@nextanimation.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
