      <title>US deploys B-52 bomber over South Korea after North Korea&#x2019;s nuclear test</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twThe United States deployed a B-52 bomber over South Korea on Sunday in a show of force after North Korea allegedly carried out a nuclear test last week.The B-52 bomber, capable of carrying nuclear weapons and based in Guam, was deployed to Osan on Sunday. The city is south of Seoul and about 62 miles from the North Korean border, Reuters reported.The bomber, flanked by a U.S. F-16 fighter jet and a South Korean F-15 fighter jet, flew low over Osan Air Base before returning to Guam.“This was a demonstration of the ironclad U.S. commitment to our allies in South Korea, in Japan, and to the defense of the American homeland,” Adm. Harry B. Harris Jr., the commander of U.S. Pacific Command said in the statement quoted by ABC News.North Korean leader Kim Jong Un said the nuclear test was a self-defence step against a U.S. threat of nuclear war and no one had the right to criticize it.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. A B-52 bomber with nuclear weapons2. Depiction of the bomber flies to Osan from Guam; distance between Osan and border3. The bomber flying in the air with a U.S. F-16 and a South Korean F-15VOICEOVER (in English): “A U.S. B-52 bomber, capable of carrying nuclear weapons..”“...based in Guam, was deployed to Osan on Sunday. The city is south of Seoul and about 62 miles from the North Korean border.”“The bomber, flanked by a U.S. F-16 fighter jet and a South Korean F-15 fighter jet, flew low over Osan Air Base before returning to Guam.”SOURCES: Reuters, ABC Newshttp://www.reuters.com/article/us-northkorea-nuclear-idUSKCN0UN0Y420160110http://abcnews.go.com/International/us-52-flyover-south-korea-response-north-korean/story?id=36192658***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
