      <title>World&#x2019;s tallest evacuation chute measures 81 meters</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twA Danish company has just received approval for a record-breaking 81-meter-tall evacuation chute for use on oil rigs that could help save lives in the event of a future disaster similar to the Deepwater Horizon explosion in 2010.The new escape chute, manufactured by Viking Life-Saving, is designed for oil rigs measuring up to 81 meters tall, or about the same height as the Statue of Liberty.In the event of an emergency, the chute automatically drops down to the level of the water, where a life raft inflates ready for the evacuees.The workers then slide down the chute one by one, before gathering in the life raft, where they can float away and wait to be rescued.The new chute is capable of evacuating 146 people in just 10 minutes.The manufacturer says the new chutes are in response to the ever increasing heights of new rigs, which make escape boats no longer viable.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Height comparison of offshore oil rig and Statue of Liberty2. Depiction of the escape chute and life raft deployment3. Depiction of the crew travelling down the chute4. Chute capacity (146 people evacuated in 10 minutes)VOICEOVER (in English): “The record-breaking new escape chute, manufactured by Danish company Viking Life-Saving, is designed for oil rigs measuring up to 81m, or about the same height as the Statue of Liberty.”“In the event of an emergency, the chute automatically drops down to the level of the water, where a life raft inflates ready for the evacuees.”“The workers then slide down the chute one by one, before gathering in the life raft, where they can float away and wait to be rescued.”“The new chute is capable of evacuating 146 people in just 10 minutes.”SOURCES: GCaptainhttp://gcaptain.com/2016/01/07/worlds-tallest-evacuation-chute-approved-to-81-meters-photos/#.Vo8SUpN96CS***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please cont