      <title>NASA says mysterious star is likely surrounded by comets</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twMysterious debris surrounding a star that scientists earlier this year posited may be an alien megastructure is actually likely to be just comets, according to NASA.The space agency used its Spitzer Space Telescope to observe infrared light data from the star, KIC 8462852, to test for other possibilities of what the debris maybe. NASA explained that if planetary impact or an asteroid collision was the cause of the debris, there would have been excess infrared light surrounding the star. Spitzer found none.“Spitzer has observed all of the hundreds of thousands of stars where Kepler hunted for planets, in the hope of finding infrared emission from circumstellar dust,” Michael Werner, the Spitzer project scientist at NASA, said in a press release on the Jet Propulsion Laboratory’s website.While NASA doesn't specifically rule out the megastructure theory, it gives more credence to the idea that comets of varying shapes and sizes are what caused the anomaly initially observed.The research was led by Massimo Marengo of Iowa State University and has been accepted for publication in the Astrophysical Journal Letters.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Star surrounded by alien megastructure, then by comets2. Spitzer telescope observing star3. Asteroid collision, infrared image 4. Comets in front of the starVOICEOVER (in English): “An anomaly around the star KIC 8462852 that scientists earlier this year posited may be evidence of an alien megastructure is likely to be a swarm of comets, new research suggests.”“NASA used the Spitzer Space Telescope to observe data from the star in infrared light to test for other possibilities of what the debris may be.”“NASA says that if planetary impact or an asteroid collision was the cause of the debris, there would have been excess infrared light surrounding the star. Spitzer found none.”“While NASA doesn't rule out the megastructure theory, it gives more weight to the notion that comets of varying shapes and sizes are what caused the anomaly initially observed.”SOURCES: NASA, CNNhttp://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?feature=4777http://edition.cnn.com/2015/11/25/us/nasa-space-anomaly-comets/***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
