      <title>Dam collapse triggers toxic mudslide, dozens killed</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twDozens are feared dead after a dam holding back waste water from an iron ore mine in rural Brazil broke, spilling toxic mud into a town.The New York Times reports that homes and vehicles in the small mining town of Mariana in Minas Gerais were smothered in thick rivers of toxic mud on Thursday after a dam collapse around 4:20 p.m. sent industrial effluent four miles down the mountain. More than 600 people from the nearby town of Bento Rodrigues had to be evacuated as a result.The dam, owned by Brazilian Samarco -- a joint venture between iron ore miners Vale of Brazil and Australia's BHP -- ruptured for unknown reasons.The surface area of the spillage -- mining waste made up of metal fillings, water, and chemicals -- was equivalent to 10 football fields, according to AFP.At least 17 were killed in the disaster, with more than 50 injured. Reuters reports that 45 others still missing.Search and rescue efforts are ongoing, but teams are hampered by the lack of electricity and difficulty in accessing affected areas. RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Brazil on map2. Dam burst, town evacuated3. Amount of mud in dam4. No. of dead, injured, missingVOICEOVER (in English): “Homes and vehicles in a mining town in southeastern Brazil were smothered in thick rivers of toxic mud on Thursday...”“...after a dam collapse around 4:20 p.m. sent industrial sludge four miles down the mountain, affecting more than 600 people from the nearby town of Bento Rodrigues.”“The surface area of the spillage -- mining waste made up of metal fillings, water, and chemicals -- was equivalent to 10 football fields.”“At least 17 were killed in the disaster, with more than 50 injured, and 45 others still missing.”SOURCES: Reuters, BBC, Wall Street Journal, Bloomberg, New York Times, AFP (via Yahoo), Voice of Americahttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/11/06/vale-sa-bhp-billiton-dam-idUSL1N1303CA20151106#PjpPQALbKLicUldo.97http://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-34742272http://www.wsj.com/articles/mining-company-samarcos-dam-bursts-in-brazil-1446763579http://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-11-05/samarco-says-dam-in-brazil-burst-teams-are-working-on-sitehttp://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2015/11/05/world/americas/ap-lt-brazil-dam-bursts.html?_r=0http://news.yahoo.com/least-17-dead-dam-bursts-brazil-mining-waste-022224741.htmlhttp://www.voanews.com/content/brazilian-dam-bursts-engulfing-town-red-sludge/3041521.html***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
