      <title>Samsung unveils wearable batteries</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twA subsidiary of South Korean multinational conglomerate Samsung unveiled a new range of batteries at an exhibition in Seoul last week that are designed to be worn.The batteries are known as the Band and the Stripe, which were developed by Samsung SDI, according to Geek. They can be attached to current smart wearables.The Band is designed for smartwatches and can provide up to 50 percent more battery life. The Stripe is just 0.3 mm in depth and can be bent into different shapes, which is suitable for accessories such as necklaces and headbands, Geek reported.Both batteries are prototypes, and no official release dates have been set.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Displaying the Band and the Stripe batteries2. Depiction of the Band provides 50% more battery life to a smartwatch3. Depth of the Stripe4. Depiction of the Stripe can be applied on necklaces and headbandsVOICEOVER (in English): “Samsung SDI has unveiled a new range of batteries called the Band and the Stripe, which can be attached to current smart wearables.”“The Band is designed for smartwatches and is designed to provide up to 50 percent more battery life.”“The Stripe is just 0.3 mm in depth and can be bent into different shapes, making it suitable for accessories such as necklaces and headbands.”SOURCES: Business Insider, Geekhttp://www.businessinsider.com/samsung-band-and-stripe-batteries-2015-10http://www.geek.com/mobile/samsungs-stripe-battery-bends-like-a-piece-of-fiber-1637822/***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
