      <title>DrumPants wearable fabric sensors gives voices to the speech-impaired</title>
      <description><![CDATA[EDIT NUMBER: 1833SLUG/TITLE: US-USA-TECHNOLOGY-DRUMPANTS-TAPSREUTERS HEADLINE: DrumPants wearable fabric sensors gives voices to the speech-impaired LOCATION: USARESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twDrumPants TAPS is an app aimed at giving a voice to speech-impaired individuals. The device connects to wearable fabric sensors called DrumPants.  “Hitting a DrumPants trigger could now trigger a phrase on your phone,” says Tyler Freeman, creator of DrumPants and co-founder of Tappur, a San Francisco startup. TAPS stands for “trigger activated personal assistant.” Freeman collaborated with Michael Zinn, a rehabilitation support worker based in Canada, to develop the TAPS app.    “People with brain injuries who had difficulty speaking, they can use this,” he says. “TAPS gives them an easy way to communicate,” The device works when the user straps the fabric sensors to their body, or use Velcro to attach them to the user’s clothes. These fabric sensors are velocity sensitive, meaning the harder they’re hit, the louder they produce sound. The system uses a “text-to-speech” engine, so it can be programmed to say what the user wants when phrases are typed into the app on a smartphone or tablet. The phrases are then assigned to each trigger. A Bluetooth enabled control unit connects the triggers to the app. This results in the app speaking for the user when the sensors are tapped. TAPS is currently beta testing. Since individuals with limited mobility still need help programming each trigger, according to Zinn, they’re developing an external keyboard for mobile devices. RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. DrumPants demo by Tyler Freeman, Creator of DrumPants and Co-founder of Tappur2. DrumPants TAPS demo by Freeman3. Freeman interview4. DrumPants TAPS app5. Freeman interview6.  Animation depicting DrumPants TAPS7. Next stage of DrumPants TAPSVOICEOVER (in English): [TITLE CUT - ALL CAPS, TWO DECKS, 33 CHARACTERS PER DECK]WEARABLE DEVI