      <title>Sinkhole swallows car and caravan at Australian campground</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twA large sinkhole opened up near Queensland’s Rainbow Beach, terrifying campers along Inskip Point on Saturday.Fishermen were the first to notice the shoreline quickly receding into the ocean around 10:30 pm, the Brisbane Times reports. Casey Hughes told ABC news it sounded like thunder as the sinkhole was opening.The sinkhole was 150 meters long, 50 meters wide and three meters deep. The sinkhole swallowed up one car, a caravan, a camper trailer and several tents. 140 people were evacuated from the campground, but no injuries were reported. Most of the campers were able to move their vehicles out of harm’s way before their campsites were submerged in water. RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Location and overview2. Fishermen notice sinkhole developing3. Sinkhole develops4. Dimensions of sinkhole5. A car, caravan, camper trailer and tent swallowed6. 140 people were evacuated safelyVOICEOVER (in English): “A large sinkhole opened up near Queensland’s Rainbow Beach, terrifying campers along Inskip Point on Saturday.”“Fishermen were the first to notice the shoreline quickly receding into the ocean around 10:30 pm.” “Casey Hughes told ABC news it sounded like thunder as the sinkhole was opening.”“The sinkhole was 150 meters long, 50 meters wide and three meters deep.”“The sinkhole swallowed up one car, a caravan, a camper trailer and several tents.” “140 people were evacuated from the campground, but no injuries were reported.” SOURCES: ABC, Sunshine Coast Daily, Brisbane Timeshttp://mobile.abc.net.au/news/2015-09-27/major-sinkhole-swallows-vehicles-on-qld-coast/6807536http://www.sunshinecoastdaily.com.au/news/campsite-terror-inskip-sinkhole-swallows-caravan/2787981/http://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/queensland/car-no-longer-visible-in-dramatic-inskip-point-sinkhole-ranger-20150927-gjvu6b.html***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please cont