      <title>Japan develops world&#x2019;s first portable electric vehicle</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twTOKYO, JAPAN- Japanese start-up Cocoa Motors plans to release the world’s first portable electric vehicle, the ‘Walkcar’. The walkcar weighs between 2 to 3kg (4.4 lb to 6.6lb). Despite it’s lightweight design, the portable electric vehicle can carry loads of up to 120kg(265lb). It can travel at 10kph (6.2 mph) at top speed, for up to 12 km (7.41 miles) on a single three-hour charge. Walkcar does not require a parking space as it can be carried in a bag or by hand. It is intended for use in public places such as airports and amusement parks.Customers will be able to begin reserving their device starting in October 2015, with each one costing around $800.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. 新しく発売予定の電気自動車は持ち運びが可能。かばんに入れることができる。2. 薄くて軽いが、重さは120キロ（265ポンド）まで耐えられる、3時間充電すれば、12キロメートル（7.4マイル）まで移動が可能。最高速度は時速10キロ3. 駐車場が必要ない4. 空港などでの使用を想定RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. World’s smallest electric vehicle “Walkcar”, can be carried in a bag or by hand.2. The Walkcar can carry loads up to 120kg. It can reach 10kph (6.2 mph) at top speed and travel up to 12 km (7.4 mi) on a single charge3. Parking space is not needed.4. Can be used in various public places such as airports. VOICEOVER (in English): A miniature portable electric vehicle called the “Walkcar” will go on sale in Japan this autumn.Japanese start-up Cocoa Motors recently launched a crowdfunding campaign in an attempt to begin manufacturing the “Walkcar”, a portable electric vehicle.The walkcar weighs between 2 to 3kg (4.4 lb to 6.6lb). Despite it’s lightweight design, the portable electric vehicle can carry loads of up to 120kg(265lb). It can travel at 10kph (6.2 mph) at top speed, for up to 12 km (7.41 miles) on a single three-hour charge. The “Walkcar” can be carried by hand and therefore does not require a parking space.The designer says the “Walkcar” can be used in public places such as theme parks and airports.SOURCES: http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/08/10/us-japan-walkcar-idUSKCN0QF1BC20150810http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/08/07/us-japan-walkcar-idUSKCN0QC1MS20150807http://www.bbc.com/news/technology-33849622http://gizmodo.com/a-tiny-personal-transporter-that-looks-like-a-macbook-y-1722720141***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
