      <title>World's longest water slide finds its new home at Action Park in Vernon, New Jersey</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twThe most awesome water slide in the world has found a new home at Action Park in Vernon, New Jersey. New Zealander Jimi Hunt, the co-founder of Live More Awesome charity, said that he had the slide constructed to raise awareness about depression and mental illness. The Guinness Book of World Records has recognized it as the longest in the world.It takes three days to fully set up the slide, which measures 1,975 feet long and uses about a thousand gallons of water per hour in order to facilitate sliding speeds reaching up to 40 miles per hour. It is made from the same PVC material that bouncy castles use. Up to 15 air blowers are used to keep it inflated.Initial test runs with park employees proved successful, but the slide still requires the state’s approval. Chances are it may be open to the public in 2016. RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Man slides and the length of the slide is measured2. A modified snow machines trickle water3. The slide is moved from New Zealand to USA4. Air blowers keep the slide inflated5. Park employees enjoy the slideVOICEOVER (in English): The slide measures 1,975 feet in length and is wide enough for one adult.Modified snow-making machines pour a thousand gallons of water per hour onto the slide, allowing riders to reach speeds of 35 to 40 miles per hour. Jimi Hunt, the creator of the slide, brought it from his homeland of New Zealand to its current location at Action Park in Vernon, New Jersey.According to Hunt, the waterslide uses 15 air blowers to stay inflated and takes two to three days to fully set up.Though initial test runs with park employees were successful, the waterslide still requires state approval before opening to the public.SOURCES: Daily Mail, WGNOhttp://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3159952/World-s-longest-inflatable-water-slide-comes-New-Jersey-Action-Park.htmlhttp://wgno.com/2015/07/13/the-worlds-longest-inflatable-water-slide-is-now-in-the-us/]]></description>
