      <title>U.S. Supreme Court upholds execution drug midazolam</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twThe U.S. Supreme Court has upheld the use of an execution drug that has been previously implicated in flawed executions.In Glossip v. Gross, three prisoners in Oklahoma argued that midazolam failed to achieve the level of unconsciousness required for surgery, creating risk of severe pain and suffering, the BBC reported.Midazolam is supposed to induce unconsciousness before other drugs are injected to stop a person’s breathing and their heart.Eight U.S. states, including Oklahoma, have either used midazolam or have proposed using the drug, the New York Times reported.Some U.S. states reintroduced other controversial methods, such as the gas chamber and firing squad during the shortage of various drugs, according to the BBC.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. U.S. turns to midazolam after EU bans the sale of lethal injection drugs 2. Midazolam supposed to induce unconsciousness during lethal injection 3. Oklahoma highlighted on map 4. Three inmates have flawed executions5. Eight states allow the use of midazolamVOICEOVER (in English): [TITLE CUT]“Several U.S. states began turning to midazolam after the EU banned the sale of products used in lethal injections.”“Midazolam is supposed to induce unconsciousness before other drugs are injected into a person to stop their breathing and their heart.”“In Glossip v. Gross, three prisoners in Oklahoma argued that midazolam failed to achieve the level of unconsciousness required for surgery, creating risk of severe pain and suffering.”“Eight U.S. states, including Oklahoma, have either used midazolam or have proposed using the drug.”SOURCES: BBC, New York Timeshttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-33314067http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2015/01/28/us/oklahoma-death-penalty-case.html***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and 