      <title>Samsung unveils &#x2018;see-through&#x2019; trucks</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twSamsung is seeking regulatory approval for a new invention that literally makes trucks see-through and which the tech giant hopes may improve road safety.Dubbed the “Safety Truck”, Samsung installed a wireless camera to the front of a truck, which sends a live video feed to a video wall made of four exterior monitors on the back of the truck. Drivers behind the truck can see clearly what is going on in front of the truck and thus can decide when to overtake safely, according to an official blog of Samsung.The truck was developed and tested in Argentina, where traffic accident rates are among the highest in the world, CBS News reported.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. A car fails to overtake a truck on a single-lane road2. Camera and monitors installed on a truck3. A car sees the image on monitors and overtakes a truck 4. A car sees an animal crossing the road on the monitors on truckVOICEOVER (in English): “Overtaking trucks on a single-lane road can be extremely dangerous as it is often difficult to see the road condition in front of the truck.”“To solve this problem, Samsung has installed a wireless camera to the front of the truck, which sends a live video feed to a video wall made of four exterior monitors on the back of the truck.”“This enables drivers behind the truck to see clearly what is going on in front of the truck and thus can decide when to overtake safely.”“It may also reduce the risk of accidents caused by animals crossing roads.”SOURCES: Samsung Tomorrow, The Verge, CBS Newshttp://global.samsungtomorrow.com/the-safety-truck-could-revolutionize-road-safety/http://www.theverge.com/2015/6/21/8820059/samsung-road-safety-truck-prototypehttp://www.cbsnews.com/news/could-samsungs-see-through-safety-semi-truck-prevent-accidents/***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7