      <title>Skinny jeans sends an Australian woman to the hospital</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twDoctors are warning of the dangers associated with wearing tight jeans after a 35-year-old ‘fashion victim’ in Australia had to be hospitalized for several days with severe numbness in her legs after spending hours squatting to clean out cupboards while wearing skinny jeans.Medical professionals say that skinny jeans can cause a condition called ‘compartment syndrome,’ where swollen muscles can end up severely damaging nerves in the leg.The squatting position, together with tight jeans, caused the woman’s muscles to swell, constricting the blood vessels and causing decreased blood supply to the legs. Looser pants would have allowed the muscles to expand to the side and relieve pressure on the blood vessels inside.The combination of swollen muscles and skinny jeans also placed pressure on two important nerves in the calf - the common peroneal nerve and the tibial nerve. This crushed the nerves and brought about a loss of feeling in the woman’s calves and feet.As the woman walked home that evening, she found that she couldn’t move her legs and feet properly and collapsed on the road.Doctors studied the woman’s nerves after she was hospitalized and found that there were blockages in her leg nerves. The woman spent a few days in the hospital recovering before she was able to walk on her own again.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Woman kneeling and cleaning cupboard2. Woman’s blood supply to lower legs is reduced3. Swollen muscles push on nerve in the back of the leg4. Woman collapses on the way homeVOICEOVER (in English): “The warnings about skinny jeans come after an Australian woman encountered severe numbness in her legs and had to be hospitalized after spending hours squatting to clean out cupboards.”“The squatting position, together with her tight jeans, caused the woman’s muscles to swell. The swelling constricted the blood vessels and led to decreased blood supply in the lower legs. Looser pants would have allowed the muscles to expand to the side and relieve pressure on the blood vessels inside.”“The combination of swollen muscles and skinny jeans also placed pressure on the nerves in the calf, crushing the nerves and causing a loss of feeling in the woman’s legs.”“As the woman walked home that evening, she found that she couldn’t move her legs and feet properly and collapsed on the road.”SOURCES: Time, The Sydney Morning Herald, The Guardian, Business Insiderhttp://time.com/3930558/skinny-jeans-harms/http://www.smh.com.au/national/health/close-call-skinny-jeans-wearer-hospitalised-with-leg-weakness-and-nerve-damage-20150623-ghue8m?skin=dumb-phonehttp://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/jun/22/skinny-jeans-bad-for-your-health-scientific-evidencehttp://www.businessinsider.com/skinny-jeans-are-bad-for-your-health-2015-6***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
