      <title>US woman begins a 6,000-mile voyage across the Pacific</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twA US woman began a 6,000 mile voyage across the Pacific from Japan on Sunday in an attempt to become the first woman to cross the Pacific Ocean alone in a rowboat.US athlete Sonya Baumstein began her trip from Choshi in Japan on Sunday headed for San Francisco. She aims to finish the epic cross-Pacific journey by late September, Newser reported.Her gear and supplies include six oars, 900 dehydrated meals, 180 drink supplements, 60 liters of spare water and two desalination machines as well as 20 bags of clothing, according to the Expedition Pacific website.The boat is integrated with a system of devices that takes readings including seawater and temperature, as well as the boat’s GPS coordinates every 10 seconds. The information will be uploaded via satellite every hour throughout the journey, according to the website.Only two men have successfully crossed the Pacific Ocean in rowboats out of the 16 attempts in the past, Reuters reported.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Route of the expedition2. Details of Baumstein’s gear and supplies3. Baumstein rows 12 to 16 hours per day4. Illustration of the boat taking samples of seawater and temperature every 10 seconds5. Illustration of the data is sent to satellite every hourVOICEOVER (in English): “US athlete Sonya Baumstein began her trip from Choshi in Japan on Sunday headed for San Francisco. She aims to finish the epic 6,000 mile cross-Pacific journey by late September.”“Her gear and supplies include six oars, 900 dehydrated meals, 180 drink supplements, 60 liters of spare water and two desalinating machines as well as 20 bags of clothing.”“Baumstein will be rowing for 12 to 16 hours per day.”“The boat is integrated with a system of devices that sample the seawater and temperature, as well as charting the boat’s GPS coordinates every 10 seconds. The information will be uploaded via satellite every hour throughout the journey.”SOURCES: Reuters, Newser, Expedition Pacifichttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/06/07/us-usa-rowing-journey-idUSKBN0ON0YI20150607http://www.newser.com/story/207910/rower-begins-6k-mile-quest-to-cross-pacific.htmlhttp://expeditionpacific.com/discover/the-boat***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
