      <title>Texas Senate votes to allow concealed carry of guns on campuses</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twThe Texas Senate voted on Saturday to allow individuals with a concealed carry license, to bring handguns onto university campuses. Current Texas law prohibits guns in federal buildings, public sporting events, bars, and on school property.  The 21 years of age requirement for a concealed carry permit, means many college students would be ineligible. The proposed bill would allow for college administrators to designate a “gun-free zone” on their campus.The bill will likely pass through the House of Representatives on Sunday before it’s signed into law by Texas Governor Greg Abbott. A related bill allowing for open carrying of handguns was passed by both the Texas Senate and the House. Abbott expressed his enthusiasm to sign the open-carry bill via Twitter. The governor is also expected to sign off on the campus concealed carry bill. RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Bill passing through Senate2. Details of current Texas concealed carry law3. Student carrying a concealed weapon4. Campus president designating “no-gun zone”5. Bill goes to House of Representatives and Governor AbbottVOICEOVER: "The Texas Senate voted on Saturday to allow individuals with a concealed carry license, to bring handguns onto university campuses.""Current Texas law prohibits guns in federal buildings, public sporting events, bars, and on school property."  "The 21 years of age requirement for a concealed carry permit, means many college students would be ineligible.""The proposed bill would allow for college administrators to designate a “gun-free zone” on their campus.""The bill will likely pass through the House of Representatives on Sunday before it’s signed into law by Texas Governor Greg Abbott."SOURCES: REUTERS, NRAhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/05/31/us-usa-texas-guns-idUSKBN0OG00720150531https://www.nraila.org/gun-laws/state-gun-laws/texas/***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editor