      <title>China warns US plane to turn away from South China Sea islands airspace</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twChina’s navy issued multiple demands to a U.S. surveillance aircraft on Wednesday to leave the airspace near islands in Southeast Asia’s most dangerous flashpoint.An American P-8A Poseidon was conducting a surveillance flight over facilities on reclaimed land that China is building in the contested South China Sea.In response, China’s navy issued eight warnings and told the aircraft’s pilots to turn away. At its lowest point, the Poseidon reached an altitude of 15,000 feet.Footage taken by the Poseidon shows construction activity on the islands and Chinese navy ships nearby. On Fiery Cross Reef, the footage shows that a military barracks, lookout tower and runway have already been built.The 3,000 metre-long runway could be fully operation by the end of the year and long enough for any aircraft in the Chinese military to take off from and land on.The U.S. is now considering moving aerial and surface missions closer to the islands. Until now, the U.S. has stayed outside the islands’ 12 nautical mile territorial zone.Some Analysts warned the U.S. actions might escalate tensions in the region. The US says China’s grab for territory risks setting a precedent in which larger countries are free to muscle in on and intimidate smaller ones.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. P-8A Poseidon approaching artificial islands2. A Chinese radio operator warning US aircraft pilot to leave3. The P-8A Poseidon altitude4. Construction works on the Chinese islands 5. Fiery Cross Reef island’s military barrack, lookout tower and runway6. The US aircraft Poseidon and warship approaching the islandsVOICEOVER: “A US P-8A Poseidon aircraft was conducting a surveillance flight over reclaimed-land islands China is building in the contested South China Sea.”“In response, China’s navy issued eight warnings and told the aircraft’s pilots to turn away.”“At its lowest point, the Poseidon reached an altitude of 15,000 feet.”“Footage taken by the Poseidon shows construction activities on the islands and Chinese navy ships nearby.”“On Fiery Cross Reef island, for instance, military barracks, a lookout tower and a runway have already been built.”“The U.S. is now considering pushing its aerial and surface missions closer to the islands. Until now, the U.S. has stayed outside the islands’ 12 nautical mile territorial zone.”SOURCES: CNN, THE GUARDIAN, REUTERS, http://edition.cnn.com/2015/05/20/politics/south-china-sea-navy-flight/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/may/21/china-warns-us-plane-to-leave-airspace-over-disputed-islandshttp://uk.reuters.com/article/2015/05/21/uk-southchinasea-usa-china-idUKKBN0O60B220150521***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
