      <title>Security researcher tells FBI he hacked into airplane controls</title>
      <description><![CDATA[For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twSecurity researcher Chris Roberts was kicked off a United Airlines flight for a tweet about hacking the plane’s electronic system. Chris Roberts told FBI agents that he’s hacked into commercial in-flight entertainment, or IFE, systems approximately 15-20 times.Roberts acquired access to the IFE system by removing a panel underneath passenger seats. He then connected a modified Ethernet cable from the IFE system to his computer. Using default username and passwords, Roberts gained access to other flight systems such as cabin and thrust controls. On one occasion he caused a plane to temporarily fly sideways, Roberts told FBI agents.  Roberts was removed from a United Airlines flight from Chicago to Syracuse, New York last month after publishing a tweet suggesting he might compromise the plane’s electronic system.The FBI confiscated Roberts computer equipment while the search warrant was being processed. Roberts is the founder of One World Labs. They protect people and organizations from cyber threats. No charges have been filed against Roberts in connection to the aircraft systems hack.  RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Roberts gaining access to panel2. Roberts connecting to IFE3. Controlling from his laptop4. Flight compromised5. Roberts publishes a tweet6. FBI agents confiscate itemsVOICEOVER (in English): “Roberts acquired access to the IFE system by removing a panel underneath passenger seats.” “He then connected a modified Ethernet cable from the IFE system to his computer.”“Using default username and passwords, Roberts gained access to other flight systems such as cabin and thrust controls.” “On one occasion he caused a plane to temporarily fly sideways, Roberts told FBI agents.”  “Roberts was removed from a flight after publishing a tweet suggesting he might compromise the plane’s electronic system.”“The FBI confiscated Roberts computer equipment while the search warrant was being processed.” SOURCES: Wired, APTNhttp://www.wired.com/2015/05/feds-say-banned-researcher-commandeered-plane/http://aptn.ca/news/2015/05/15/hacker-told-f-b-made-plane-fly-sideways-cracking-entertainment-system/***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
