      <title>Toyota, Nissan recall over 5 million cars for faulty airbags</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twToyota Motor Corp. and Nissan Motor Co. have issued a global recall of millions of vehicles over problems with their airbags, which are designed by Japanese supplier Takata Corps.Toyota said on Wednesday that it is recalling around 5 million vehicles globally due to of airbag problems. The recall will affect 35 Toyota models globally. Nissan has recalled another 1.56 million vehicles globally for the same airbag problems. The inside of an airbag’s inflator assembly, which is located underneath the steering wheel, is filled with propellant granules and propellants. Unlike propellants made by most other brands, Takata-designed propellants are made from ammonium nitrate. If exposed to high humidity, the propellants can end up damaged or cracked, this causes them to produce too much pressure inside the inflator, causing it to crack and explode.When the airbag inflates, pieces of the damaged inflator may fly at the driver and passenger like shrapnel, putting people in a crash at greater risk in injury.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Passenger and driver-side airbags experience problems2. Location of an inflator assembly and propellant granules within the inflator heating up the propellants3. Propellant exposed to high humidity and causing damage to the inflator4. Airbag inflating and pieces of the inflator hitting a driver and his passengerVOICEOVER (in English): “In the recalled vehicles, front passenger and driver-side airbags may deploy abnormally.”“The inside of an airbag’s inflator assembly, which is located underneath the steering wheel, is filled with propellant granules and propellants. Unlike propellants made by most other brands, Takata-designed propellants are made from ammonium nitrate.”“If exposed to high humidity, the propellants can end up damaged, this causes them to produce too much pressure inside the inflator, causing it to crack and explode.”“When the airbag inflates, 