      <title>Tennessee Subway installs anti-robber DNA spray system</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.tw A Subway restaurant in Knoxville, Tennessee just became the first U.S. business to implement an intruder spray system, a security device that sprays robbers with synthetic DNA.“It’s exciting to lead in something that’s not just on the food side of things,” Subway Director of Operations A.J. Underwood told WATE. SelectaDNA, the distributor of the device, has already set up similar security systems in 30 countries around the world, according to the company’s website. The system comes with warning signs and an alarm. But if a robber still manages to steal from the store, the security device sprays him or her with an odorless and colorless DNA mist. The DNA markings stick to the thief’s clothing fibers and skin cracks and are only visible under a UV light. Even if a criminal is stopped 7 weeks after the crime, an officer can still spot the DNA markings. Every system has a unique DNA code, so the robber can be traced back to a specific location. Subway plans to install the device at hundreds of locations to thwart robberies, according to True Crime. RUNDOWN SHOWS:1.DNA security spray system scanning inside of restaurant 2.Robber leaving restaurant, pull-out showing DNA code of spray system 3.Security system spraying robber 4.DNA spray sticking to robber’s clothing fibers and skin cracks5.Cop with UV light questioning robber  6.Cop linking robber’s DNA markings to security system’s DNAVOICEOVERA Knoxville Subway just became the first U.S. business to implement the intruder spray system - A Security device that sprays robbers with synthetic DNA that links them to the crime. The odorless and colorless spray is only visible under a UV light. The marks are shower-proof as they get into the intruder’s clothing fibers and skin cracks. Even if a criminal is stopped 7 weeks after the crime, an officer can still spot the DNA markings. Every system has a unique DNA code, so the robber can be traced back to a specific location. SOURCES: ABC 6, True Crime, SelectaDNAhttp://wate.com/2015/05/11/new-security-system-makes-nationwide-debut-at-knoxville-subway/http://truecrime.io9.com/restaurant-installs-intruder-spray-to-tag-burglars-wi-1703737555https://www.selectadna.co.uk/dna-intruder-sprays/selectadna-spray-warning-sign-foamex-400x300mm***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------]]></description>
