      <title>The science behind Kylie Jenner&#x2019;s plump lips</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twKylie Jenner, the youngest “Keeping up with the Kardashians” star, admitted to using lip fillers, after insisting for months her plump lips were all natural.“It’s just an insecurity of mine, and it’s what I wanted to do,” the 17-year-old said during a sneak peek of an upcoming episode.Jenner admitted to using temporary lip augmentation, which likely means a medical professional numbed her lips and then injected a hyaluronic acid. There are several types of hyaluronic acids, but they all work by essentially adding moisture and cushioning to the skin.Hyaluronic acid -- which does not strip the skin the way most acids do -- is a naturally-occurring polysaccharide in the eyes, joints and in between the skin cells, according to a feature by Beauty Editor. It acts as a smoothing agent for skin, and as humans age, our bodies produce less and less of it.Injection results typically last between six and nine months before a patient needs another lip augmentation, New York City plastic surgeon Dr. Matthew Schulman told People.Side effects can include bruising, scarring and infections. But the procedure seems to be safer than the Kylie Jenner Lip Challenge.“I don’t think there’s a safety concern,” Schulman said of Jenner’s lip filler treatment. “I think the bigger concern with her being 17 is more of a psychological concern: whether she’s old enough or mature enough to undergo body transformation.” The next “Kardashians” episode airs Sunday at 9 EST on E!. RUNDOWN SHOWS:1.A syringe injecting fluid into a person’s top lip2.Fluid filling the lip3.Hyaluronic acid compounds moving around in the lips4.Highlights showing naturally-occurring acid in eyes, joints and space between cells 5.Lips shrinking over 6-month period 6.Red highlights showing potential injury around lips "Kylie Jenner admitted to using temporary lip augmentation -- which likely means a medical professional numbed her lips and then injected a hyaluronic acid." "Hyaluronic acid works by essentially adding moisture and cushioning to the skin.""It’s a naturally-occurring carbohydrate in our eyes… joints… and the spaces between our skin cells." "Cosmetic results typically last about 6 months before the patient needs a touch-up.Side effects can include bruising around the lips, scarring and even infections on rare occassion." SOURCES: Fox, People, LA Timeshttp://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2015/05/07/kylie-jenner-needed-her-mothers-permission-for-lip-fillers/http://stylenews.peoplestylewatch.com/2015/05/07/kylie-jenner-lip-fillers-plastic-surgeron-reacts/http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/gossip/la-et-mg-kylie-jenner-lip-filler-20150506-story.html***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
