      <title>Baby who lived only 100 minutes becomes Britain&#x2019;s youngest organ donor</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twThe parents of Teddy Houlston, a twin boy born without a brain, decided to donate his organs when he died just 100 minutes after his birth, making him the youngest organ donor in Britain.Jess Evans from Cardiff, was pregnant with twin boys and 12 weeks into her pregnancy when she was told that one of the boys was suffering from anencephaly, a rare condition that halts development of the brain and skull.Evans refused an abortion and the boys were born on April 22 last year. The other boy was born healthy, but Teddy Houlston only lived for 100 minutes. His parents donated his kidneys and heart valves to patients in need.After Houlston died, his kidneys were extracted and transported from Cardiff to Leeds.A patient with renal failure received the organs and the child size kidneys have since grown, reaching three-quarters the size of an adult kidney.The details of the heart valve transplant have not been disclosed because of a confidentiality agreement. The surviving twin remains healthy.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Twin foetuses 2. Birth of the twins; kidneys and heart valves of Teddy Houlston3. Kidneys transported to Leeds from Cardiff 4. Kidneys growing inside the patient receiving the transplant VOICEOVER (in English): “Jess Evans from Cardiff, was pregnant with twin boys and 12 weeks into her pregnancy when she was told that one of the boys was suffering from anencephaly, a rare condition that halts development of the brain and skull.” “Evans refused an abortion and the boys were born on April 22 last year. The other boy was born healthy, but Teddy Houlston only lived for 100 minutes. His parents donated his kidneys and heart valves to patients in need.”  “After Houlston died, his kidneys were immediately extracted and transported from Cardiff to Leeds.” “A patient with renal failure received the organs and the child size kidneys have grown inside the adult, reaching three-quarters the size of a normal kidney.”  SOURCES: news.com.au, The Guardian http://www.news.com.au/lifestyle/real-life/newborn-baby-teddy-houlston-becomes-uks-youngest-organ-donor/story-fnq2o7dd-1227318623151?from=public_rss&utm_content=lifestyle&utm_campaign=socialflow&utm_source=twitter&utm_term=lifestyle&utm_medium=banner http://www.theguardian.com/society/2015/apr/23/boy-who-lived-for-100-minutes-becomes-uks-youngest-organ-donor ***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
