      <title>North Korea fires four short-range missiles into Yellow Sea</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twNorth Korea test-fired four short-range missiles on Friday, a week ahead of the U.S. defense secretary’s scheduled visit to Seoul.North Korea has test-fired four short-range missiles into the Yellow Sea from Dongchang-ri in North Pyongan province on Friday afternoon, Yonhap News reported. North Korean leader Kim Jong Un reportedly supervised the launch, according to UPI.“What the North fired are believed to be KN-02 ground-to-ship missiles, factoring in their range, speed and trajectory,” a JCS officer said on condition of anonymity to Yonhap News.The missiles reportedly flew roughly 140 km and plunged into the sea, according to Reuters. One missile may have landed in North Korea’s own territory, reported by UPI and Yonhap News.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Location of the launch and number of missiles fired2. KN-02 missiles rotating 3. Missiles being launched4. A missile plunges into the sea5. A missile lands inlandVOICEOVER: “North Korea has test-fired four short-range missiles into the Yellow Sea from Dongchang-ri in North Pyongan province on Friday.” “It is believed that North Korea fired KN-02 ground-to-ship missiles.”“The missiles reportedly flew roughly 140 km and plunged into the sea. One missile reportedly have landed in North Korea’s own territory.”SOURCES: Yonhap News, Reuters, BBC, UPIhttp://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/national/2015/04/03/44/0301000000AEN20150403008851315F.htmlhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/04/03/us-northkorea-missiles-idUSKBN0MU0TG20150403http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-32174526http://www.upi.com/Top_News/World-News/2015/04/03/North-Korea-test-fires-four-short-range-missiles-into-Yellow-Sea/9051428068946/***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
