      <title>Huge asteroid to skim past Earth</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twA huge asteroid called 2014-YB35 is set to skim past Earth on Friday.Asteroid 2014-YB35 is believed to be 1,000 meters wide, the same as the height of the Kingdom Tower currently under construction in Saudi Arabia.Travelling at more than 37,000 kph, the asteroid will barely miss Earth, according to a trajectory map released by NASA.At its closest point, it will be 2.8 million miles away from Earth, about 12 times the distance between Earth and the Moon.It is estimated that a collision with the asteroid would result in an explosive force equivalent to 15,000 megatons of TNT, which would trigger earthquakes and tsunamis and cause destruction on a global scale.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Size of Asteroid 2014-YB35 compared to Kingdom Tower2. Trajectory of the asteroid3. Distance of the asteroid from the Earth at its closest point4. Illustration of the asteroid hitting EarthVOICEOVER (in English): “Asteroid 2014-YB35 is believed to be 1,000 meters wide, the same as the height of the Kingdom Tower currently under construction in Saudi Arabia. The asteroid is set to approach Earth on Friday.” “Travelling at more than 37,000 kph, the asteroid will barely miss Earth, according to a trajectory map released by NASA.”“At its closest point, it will be 2.8 million miles away from Earth, about 12 times the distance between Earth and the Moon.”“It is estimated that a collision with the asteroid would result in an explosive force equivalent to 15,000 megatons of TNT, which would trigger earthquakes and tsunamis and cause destruction on a global scale.”SOURCES: Digital Journal, The Independent, Express.co.uk, NASAhttp://www.digitaljournal.com/science/nasa-huge-asteroid-2014-yb35-makes-close-earth-approach-friday/article/429181http://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/huge-asteroid-2014yb35-set-to-skim-past-earth-10133774.htmlhttp://www.express.co.uk/news/nature/566159/NASA-alert-asteroid-2014-YB3