      <title>Egypt builds new capital</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twDuring a recent international economic summit, Egyptian Housing Minister Mostafa Madbouly announced that Egypt will be building a new capital within the next seven years.Egyptian officials recently announced plans to build the new capital 700 square kilometers east of Cairo, between Cairo and the Suez Canal. They hope the new plans will relieve pressure on Cairo, whose metropolitan population is straining the city’s infrastructure.The United Arab Emirates helped fund the new city, which has an estimated total cost of US$45 billion. Officials say the city will also take about 5-7 years to complete.The new capital will be 12 times the size of New York’s Manhattan Island, and will include 1.1 million residential units that are expected to house up to five million people. The new capital will also include government buildings, a theme park, a solar farm, electric trains, resorts and shopping malls.Once complete, the city will be the biggest purpose-built capital to date.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Cairo experiencing a huge population growth2. Location of Egypt’s new capital3. New capital will be 12 times the size of Manhattan4. United Arab Emirates helped fund the new city5. New city will house up to 5 million people6. City will include government buildings, a theme park, solar farms, electric trains, resorts and shopping mallsVOICEOVER (in English): “Egyptian officials hope to relieve pressure on Cairo, whose metropolitan population is straining the city’s infrastructure.”“Officials recently announced plans to build the wholly new 700-square-kilometer capital city east of Cairo, between it and the Suez Canal.”“The new capital will be 12 times the size of New York’s Manhattan Island.”“The United Arab Emirates helped fund the new city, which has an estimated total cost of US$45 billion. Building the city will also take about 5-7 years to complete.”“The city will include 1.1 million residential units that are expected to house up to five million people.”“The city will also include government buildings, a theme park, a solar farm, electric trains, resorts and shopping malls.”SOURCES: The Wall Street Journal, Ahram Online, Australian Broadcasting Corporationhttp://www.wsj.com/articles/egypt-unveils-plans-for-new-capital-city-1426342865http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/3/12/125333/Business/Economy/Egypt-set-to-start-work-on-new-capital-city-in-as-.aspxhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-03-14/egyptian-government-reveals-plans-to-build-new-capital/6320144***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
