      <title>UK girl undergoes &#x2018;balloon treatment&#x2019; to remove huge birthmark</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twA 9-year-old girl in the UK had balloons inserted under her scalp as part of a novel treatment to grow new skin in order to remove a large mole covering her head.Jessica Brett was born with a mole covering about half of her head, which doctors said could be untreatable if it turned cancerous.To remove the mole, doctors from the Leicester Royal Infirmary inserted silicone balloons underneath her scalp and slowly expanded them by adding saline solution every two weeks. It took a total of six months and more than a pint and a half of saline solution to stretch her skin.Doctors then removed the balloons and the mole and covered the wound with the excess skin created by stretching the balloons.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Large mole on Jessica Brett’s head2. Balloons inserted under her scalp3. Saline solution injected into the balloons4. Balloons and the mole removedVOICEOVER (in English): “Jessica Brett was born with a mole covering about half of her head, which doctors said could become untreatable if it turned cancerous, according to reports.”“In order to remove the mole, doctors inserted silicone balloons underneath her scalp...”“...and slowly expanded them by adding saline solution every two weeks.” “Doctors then removed the balloons and the mole and covered the wound with the excess skin created by stretching the balloons.”SOURCES: Metro, The Telegraphhttp://metro.co.uk/2015/03/09/girls-trendy-hairstyle-is-actually-a-head-full-of-balloons-that-could-save-her-from-cancer-5094828/?ito=v-ahttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/health/news/11458731/UK-medical-first-as-girl-with-huge-birthmark-undergoes-pioneering-balloon-treatment-to-grow-new-skin.html***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
