      <title>Scientists discover 1000-year-old monk inside Buddha statue</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twA CT-scan of an ancient Buddha statue has led to the unique discovery of a mummified Chinese monk, dating back to the 11th century and preserved in the same position as its exterior statue. The Buddha statue, which was on display at the Drents Museum in the Dutch city of Assen, was analyzed at the Meander Medical Center in Amersfoort.A team of scientists and doctors tested the statue using CT-scan imaging and an endoscope. Amsterdam resident Erik Bruijn headed the project, according to the NL Times online.  The mummified body has been identified as Master Liuquan, a Buddhist monk who likely practiced Sokushinbutsu, or self-mummification. Radiologist Ben Heggelman took bone samples to confirm the mummy’s identification with DNA testing. The statue, which is currently visiting Hungary, will be on display in Budapest until May 2015. RUNDOWN SHOWS:Statue on display in museumStatue entering CT-scan machineCT-scan reveals image of mummyMummy on timeline between 1000 and 1100   Pull-outs of thoracic and abdominal cavitiesPaper scraps inside mummyVOICEOVER (in English): The nearly 1000-year-old Chinese Buddha statue was on display in the Drents Museum in Amsterdam.In September, the statue was moved to the Meander Medical Center for a CT-scan and endoscopic testing. The CT-scan revealed the remains of a mummified monk, sitting in the same position as the external statue. The monk has since been identified as Master Liuquan, who was part of the Chinese Meditation School in the 11th century. [CUT 5] Researchers used an endoscope to examine the thoracic and abdominal cavities of the mummy. They also found scraps of paper containing Chinese characters, where Master Liuquan’s organs had been. SOURCES: CNET, NL Times, Daily Mailhttp://www.nltimes.nl/2014/12/09/1000-year-old-chinese-mummy-gets-ct-scan-amersfoort/http://www.cnet.com/news/ct-scan-finds-mummified-monk-inside-1000-year-ol