      <title>Tesla to launch batteries that can power entire homes</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twTesla is developing a battery that can power homes with stored solar energy so that users do not need to draw power from electricity grid.According to SolarCity, the company responsible for installing the home battery systems, Tesla’s home battery charges during the daytime when solar power is plentiful. Homeowners can use the energy stored in the battery and do not need to draw power from the electricity grid during peak hours. Users can then switch back to the grid during non-peak hours.In a pilot project, a 10-kilowatt-hour battery pack is being used that can power homes for about two days in case of a power outage. The project, run by SolarCity, which is co-chaired by Tesla chief executive Elon Musk, covers 500 homes in California.Musk said the design for the battery will likely be presented to the public in the following months. Production could be just six months away, the Washington Post reported.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Battery storing power during daytime2. Battery releasing power at dusk3. Home using power from electricity grid at midnight4. Battery supplying power to home for two days during power outrage5. Pilot project puts home batteries in 500 California homesVOICEOVER (in English): “Tesla’s home battery charges during the daytime when solar power is plentiful.”“Homeowners can use the energy stored in the battery and do not need to draw power from the electricity grid during peak hours.”“Users can switch back to the grid during non-peak hours when rates are cheaper.”“In a pilot project, a 10-kilowatt-hour battery pack is being used that can power homes for about two days in case of a power outage.”“The project, run by SolarCity, a company co-chaired by Tesla chief executive Elon Musk, covers 500 homes in California.”SOURCES: SolarCity, The Verge, The Washington Posthttp://www.solarcity.com/commercial/demandlogichttp://www.theverge.com/2015/2/13/8033691/why-teslas-battery-for-your-home-should-terrify-utilitieshttp://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/the-switch/wp/2015/02/12/this-new-tesla-battery-will-power-your-home-and-maybe-the-electric-grid-too/***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
