      <title>Technology cutting hospital time for premature babies</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RESTRICTIONS: NONE For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twA medical device, known as the Pea Pod, has been developed to help premature babies grow faster and lessen their time in the neonatal intensive care unit.The Pea Pod is a medical device that uses air displacement technology to measure the body composition of premature infants, Fox News reported.A baby is first weighed by a scale equipped with the Pea Pod. The baby is then placed in an enclosed heated chamber for approximately two minutes where his or her body volume is measured by the amount of air displaced by the body inside the chamber, according to COSMED, the developer of the device. By calculating the baby’s weight versus its volume, the Pea Pod can determine the percentage of the baby’s fat versus body mass. Hospital staff can use the body composition data to design suitable nutritional supplements for the baby, Fox News reported.RUNDOWN SHOWS:1. Pea Pod scanning a baby2. Baby is being weighed on a scale on Pea Pod3. Baby is placed inside the Pea Pod chamber for 3 minutes4. Illustration of the change in air volume of the chamber5. Illustration of the baby’s body composition on the monitorVOICEOVER (in English): “The Pea Pod is a medical device that uses air displacement technology to measure the body composition of premature infants.”“The baby is first weighed by the device’s scale.”“It is then placed in an enclosed heated chamber for approximately two minutes, where its body volume is measured by the amount of air displaced by its body inside the chamber.”“By calculating the baby’s weight versus its volume, the Pea Pod can determine the percentage of the baby’s fat versus body mass.”SOURCES: Fox News, COSMED http://www.foxnews.com/health/2015/01/31/new-technology-cutting-hospital-time-for-premature-babies/http://www.cosmed.com/en/products/body-composition/pea-pod-infant-body-composition***For story suggestions please contact tips@nma.com.twFor technical and editorial support, please contact:Asia: +61 2 93 73 1841Europe: +44 20 7542 7599Americas and Latam: +1 800 738 8377]]></description>
